The paper deals with the representation of graphs using paths in a grid, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). It also involves graph theory (cs.DM) and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) in terms of analyzing the complexity of finding small grid sizes for different graph parameters. The paper also mentions results related to graph minors (cs.GT) and treewidth (cs.DC).
